    <h1>SPORTS Sports Per&#xAD;for&#xAD;mance Train&#xAD;ing</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200911/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-11"><time>2020-09-11</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Learn how to en­hance your sports per­for­mance through strength and con­di­tion­ing in this vir­tual class. Ath­letes will be coached in a va­ri­ety of move­ments (push, pull, squat, hinge and carry) to im­prove strength and power de­vel­op­ment. The train­ing plan is pro­gres­sively over­loaded to en­sure ad­e­quate adap­ta­tion to im­prove phys­i­cal per­for­mance and build up en­durance.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Google Meet WHEN: Every Sat till Sept 26, 8.30am AD­MIS­SION: $15 INFO: www.sis­tic.com.sg/ events/gm­spt2020</p>
    <p>Sim­pang River Trail</p>
    <p>Kayak­ers will take a leisurely pad­dle into one of the last river­ine man­groves on our shores and learn about the Gi­ant Fig, snails, Ru­bik’s cubes, lob­sters, and why there are plenty of ba­bies in the man­grove. The trip, or­gan­ised by eco ad­ven­ture travel com­pany Kayaka­sia, is a good in­tro­duc­tion for be­gin­ners.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Sem­bawang Park</p>
    <p>MRT: Sem­bawang WHEN: Mon, 7.30 - 11.45am AD­MIS­SION: $95 a per­son, $50 for kids un­der 12 INFO: bit.ly/3igC7kz</p>


